**Gate-by-Gate Comparison**

Using `a,b` as inputs:

+------+--------------------------------------+--------------------------------------+
| Gate | Original sequential SCOAP            | `min/max` parallel-time heuristic    |
+------+--------------------------------------+--------------------------------------+
| BUF  | `SC0(z)=SC0(a)`                      | `T0(z)=T0(a)`                        |
|      | `SC1(z)=SC1(a)`                      | `T1(z)=T1(a)`                        |
+------+--------------------------------------+--------------------------------------+
| NOT  | `SC0(z)=SC1(a)`                      | `T0(z)=T1(a)`                        |
|      | `SC1(z)=SC0(a)`                      | `T1(z)=T0(a)`                        |
+------+--------------------------------------+--------------------------------------+
| AND  | `SC0(z)=min(SC0(a),SC0(b))`          | `T0(z)=min(T0(a),T0(b))`             |
|      | `SC1(z)=SC1(a)+SC1(b)`               | `T1(z)=max(T1(a),T1(b))`             |
+------+--------------------------------------+--------------------------------------+
| NAND | `SC0(z)=SC1(a)+SC1(b)`               | `T0(z)=max(T1(a),T1(b))`             |
|      | `SC1(z)=min(SC0(a),SC0(b))`          | `T1(z)=min(T0(a),T0(b))`             |
+------+--------------------------------------+--------------------------------------+
| OR   | `SC0(z)=SC0(a)+SC0(b)`               | `T0(z)=max(T0(a),T0(b))`             |
|      | `SC1(z)=min(SC1(a),SC1(b))`          | `T1(z)=min(T1(a),T1(b))`             |
+------+--------------------------------------+--------------------------------------+
| NOR  | `SC0(z)=min(SC1(a),SC1(b))`          | `T0(z)=min(T1(a),T1(b))`             |
|      | `SC1(z)=SC0(a)+SC0(b)`               | `T1(z)=max(T0(a),T0(b))`             |
+------+--------------------------------------+--------------------------------------+
| XOR  | `SC0(z)=min(SC0(a)+SC0(b),`          | `T0(z)=min(max(T0(a),T0(b)),`        |
|      | `           SC1(a)+SC1(b))`          | `           max(T1(a),T1(b)))`       |
|      | `SC1(z)=min(SC0(a)+SC1(b),`          | `T1(z)=min(max(T0(a),T1(b)),`        |
|      | `           SC1(a)+SC0(b))`          | `           max(T1(a),T0(b)))`       |
+------+--------------------------------------+--------------------------------------+
| XNOR | `SC0(z)=min(SC0(a)+SC1(b),`          | `T0(z)=min(max(T0(a),T1(b)),`        |
|      | `           SC1(a)+SC0(b))`          | `           max(T1(a),T0(b)))`       |
|      | `SC1(z)=min(SC0(a)+SC0(b),`          | `T1(z)=min(max(T0(a),T0(b)),`        |
|      | `           SC1(a)+SC1(b))`          | `           max(T1(a),T1(b)))`       |
+------+--------------------------------------+--------------------------------------+

For `n`-input `AND/OR`, the same pattern extends naturally:
- SCOAP: `sum` when **all required inputs** are needed, `min` when **any one** is enough.
- Time heuristic: `max` when **all required inputs** are needed, `min` when **any one** is enough.

